{{Infobox football biography |name = Sean Longstaff |image = |image_size = |caption = |fullname = Sean David Longstaff<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/612828 |title=Updated squads for 2017/18 Premier League confirmed |publisher=Premier League |date=2 February 2018 |accessdate=15 February 2018}}</ref> |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1997|10|30|df=y}}<ref name=""11v11">{{cite web |url=https://www.11v11.com/players/sean-longstaff-254976/ |title=Profile |accessdate=18 January 2019 |publisher=11v11}}</ref> |birth_place = [[Newcastle upon Tyne]], England |height = {{convert|1.81|m|order=flip}}<ref name=""11v11"/> |position = [[Midfielder]] |currentclub = [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] |clubnumber = 36 |youthyears1 = {{0|0000}}–2016 |youthclubs1 = [[Newcastle United F.C. Reserves and Academy|Newcastle United]] |years1 = 2016– |clubs1 = [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] |caps1 = 9 |goals1 = 1 |years2 = 2017 |clubs2 = → [[Kilmarnock F.C.|Kilmarnock]] (loan) |caps2 = 16 |goals2 = 3 |years3 = 2017–2018 |clubs3 = → [[Blackpool F.C.|Blackpool]] (loan) |caps3 = 42 |goals3 = 8 |club-update = 09:09, 3 March 2019 (UTC) }} '''Sean David Longstaff''' (born 30 October 1997) is an English professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] as a [[midfielder]].
==Career== Longstaff began his career with the youth team of [[Newcastle United F.C. Reserves and Academy|Newcastle United]]. He moved on loan to [[Scottish Premiership]] club [[Kilmarnock F.C.|Kilmarnock]] in January 2017, along with [[Callum Roberts (footballer)|Callum Roberts]] and [[Freddie Woodman]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/38563637 |title=Kilmarnock sign Newcastle's Cal Roberts, Sean Longstaff, Freddie Woodman on loan |date=9 January 2017 |accessdate=22 July 2017 |publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> He signed on loan for [[Blackpool F.C.|Blackpool]] in July 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40687527 |title=Sean Longstaff: Blackpool sign teenage Newcastle United midfielder on loan |date=21 July 2017 |accessdate=22 July 2017 |publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref>
Longstaff impressed manager [[Rafa Benitez]] in pre-season and was rewarded with a four-year contract in November 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nufc.co.uk/news/latest-news/longstaff-signs-new-four-year-deal|title=Longstaff signs new four-year deal|website=Newcastle United Football Club}}</ref> Longstaff's first appearance for the senior team came as a substitute in a 4–0 loss to [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] in December 2018. Two weeks later, after getting his first start in the [[FA Cup]], Longstaff made his full [[Premier League]] debut away at [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]]. This was followed up by his first goal in the FA Cup replay against [[Blackburn Rovers]] before he put in a memorable performance by winning the penalty that gave Newcastle a 2–1 win over champions [[Manchester City]] in January 2019.<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/jan/15/blackburn-rovers-newcastle-united-fa-cup-match-report |title =Newcastle see off Blackburn with Joselu and Ayoze Pérez extra-time flourish|date=15 January 2019|work=Guardian|accessdate=6 March 2019}}</ref> <ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/jan/29/newcastle-united-manchester-city-premier-league-match-report |title =Newcastle’s Matt Ritchie on the spot to dent Manchester City’s title hopes|date=29 January 2019|work=Guardian|accessdate=6 March 2019}}</ref>
On 26 February 2019, Longstaff scored his first [[Premier League]] goal for Newcastle in a 2-0 win over [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]].<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/feb/26/newcastle-burnley-premier-league-match-report |title =Sean Longstaff on target as Newcastle end Burnley’s good run|date=26 February 2019|work=Guardian|accessdate=6 March 2019}}</ref>
In March 2019 Longstaff was ruled out for the rest of the [[2018–19 Newcastle United F.C. season|2018–19]] season following a knee ligament injury.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/47481878|title=Newcastle United midfielder Sean Longstaff 'likely' to miss rest of season with injury|date=7 March 2019|publisher=|via=www.bbc.co.uk}}</ref>
== Personal life == Raised in [[North Shields]], Longstaff's younger brother Matthew is also a footballer currently playing for Newcastle United. Their father [[David Longstaff|David]] is a former Great Britain [[ice hockey]] player, featuring over 100 times for the national side, and is still active as player-coach for the [[Whitley Warriors]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nufc.co.uk/teams/under-23s/matthew-longstaff |title=Newcastle United – Matthew Longstaff |publisher=Newcastle United |accessdate=18 January 2018}}</ref> Their father is also the cousin of former England international [[Alan Thompson (footballer, born 1973)|Alan Thompson]].{{citation needed|date=March 2019}}
